main event: A round, pure white object the size of a small jet aircraft was observed remaining stationary at an estimated altitude of 10,000 feet for 1 hour and 46 minutes in Steilacoom, Washington in 1956.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be at an altitude of 10,000 feet and remained stationary for nearly 2 hours, indicating an unusual behavior.
The sighting was initially speculated to be caused by the planet Venus due to the description and position of the object.
The report was sourced from a civilian observer.
No photographs were available as evidence of the sighting.
The document includes detailed observations of the object's position at different time intervals, suggesting a thorough investigation.
